{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'll start with my favorite muse, Emily Dickinson,"},{"time":3000,"text":"who said that wonder is not knowledge, neither is it ignorance."},{"time":7000,"text":"It's something which is suspended"},{"time":9000,"text":"between what we believe we can be,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and a tradition we may have forgotten."},{"time":13000,"text":"And I think, when I listen to these incredible people here,"},{"time":16000,"text":"I've been so inspired -- so many incredible ideas, so many visions."},{"time":20000,"text":"And yet, when I look at the environment outside,"},{"time":24000,"text":"you see how resistant architecture is to change."},{"time":26000,"text":"You see how resistant it is to those very ideas."},{"time":29000,"text":"We can think them out. We can create incredible things."},{"time":32000,"text":"And yet, at the end,"},{"time":34000,"text":"it's so hard to change a wall."},{"time":36000,"text":"We applaud the well-mannered box."},{"time":39000,"text":"But to create a space that never existed is what interests me;"},{"time":42000,"text":"to create something that has never been,"},{"time":45000,"text":"a space that we have never entered except in our minds and our spirits."},{"time":48000,"text":"And I think that's really what architecture is based on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"Architecture is not based on concrete"},{"time":53000,"text":"and steel and the elements of the soil."},{"time":55000,"text":"It's based on wonder."},{"time":57000,"text":"And that wonder is really what has created the greatest cities,"},{"time":60000,"text":"the greatest spaces that we have had."},{"time":62000,"text":"And I think that is indeed what architecture is. It is a story."},{"time":66000,"text":"By the way, it is a story that is told through"},{"time":69000,"text":"its hard materials."},{"time":71000,"text":"But it is a story of effort and struggle"},{"time":73000,"text":"against improbabilities."},{"time":75000,"text":"If you think of the great buildings, of the cathedrals, of the temples,"},{"time":77000,"text":"of the pyramids, of pagodas,"},{"time":79000,"text":"of cities in India and beyond,"},{"time":82000,"text":"you think of how incredible this is that that was realized"},{"time":85000,"text":"not by some abstract idea, but by people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"So, anything that has been made can be unmade."},{"time":90000,"text":"Anything that has been made can be made better."},{"time":93000,"text":"There it is: the things that I really believe"},{"time":95000,"text":"are of important architecture."},{"time":97000,"text":"These are the dimensions that I like to work with."},{"time":99000,"text":"It's something very personal."},{"time":101000,"text":"It's not, perhaps, the dimensions appreciated by art critics"},{"time":103000,"text":"or architecture critics or city planners."},{"time":105000,"text":"But I think these are the necessary oxygen"},{"time":108000,"text":"for us to live in buildings, to live in cities,"},{"time":110000,"text":"to connect ourselves in a social space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113000,"text":"And I therefore believe that optimism is what drives architecture forward."},{"time":116000,"text":"It's the only profession where you have to believe in the future."},{"time":120000,"text":"You can be a general, a politician, an economist who is depressed,"},{"time":124000,"text":"a musician in a minor key, a painter in dark colors."},{"time":127000,"text":"But architecture is that complete ecstasy that the future can be better."},{"time":132000,"text":"And it is that belief that I think drives society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"And today we have a kind of evangelical pessimism all around us."},{"time":138000,"text":"And yet it is in times like this"},{"time":140000,"text":"that I think architecture can thrive with big ideas,"},{"time":143000,"text":"ideas that are not small. Think of the great cities."},{"time":146000,"text":"Think of the Empire State Building, the Rockefeller Center."},{"time":148000,"text":"They were built in times that were"},{"time":150000,"text":"not really the best of times in a certain way."},{"time":152000,"text":"And yet that energy and power of architecture"},{"time":156000,"text":"has driven an entire social and political space that these buildings occupy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"So again, I am a believer in the expressive."},{"time":163000,"text":"I have never been a fan of the neutral."},{"time":166000,"text":"I don't like neutrality in life, in anything."},{"time":168000,"text":"I think expression."},{"time":170000,"text":"And it's like espresso coffee, you know, you take the essence of the coffee."},{"time":172000,"text":"That's what expression is."},{"time":174000,"text":"It's been missing in much of the architecture,"},{"time":176000,"text":"because we think architecture is the realm of the neutered,"},{"time":180000,"text":"the realm of the kind of a state that has no opinion,"},{"time":184000,"text":"that has no value."},{"time":186000,"text":"And yet, I believe it is the expression --"},{"time":188000,"text":"expression of the city, expression of our own space --"},{"time":191000,"text":"that gives meaning to architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"And, of course, expressive spaces are not mute."},{"time":196000,"text":"Expressive spaces are not spaces"},{"time":198000,"text":"that simply confirm what we already know."},{"time":200000,"text":"Expressive spaces may disturb us."},{"time":202000,"text":"And I think that's also part of life."},{"time":204000,"text":"Life is not just an anesthetic to make us smile,"},{"time":207000,"text":"but to reach out across the abyss of history,"},{"time":210000,"text":"to places we have never been,"},{"time":212000,"text":"and would have perhaps been, had we not been so lucky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"So again, radical versus conservative."},{"time":218000,"text":"Radical, what does it mean? It's something which is rooted,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and something which is rooted deep in a tradition."},{"time":223000,"text":"And I think that is what architecture is, it's radical."},{"time":226000,"text":"It's not just a conservation in formaldehyde"},{"time":228000,"text":"of dead forms."},{"time":230000,"text":"It is actually a living connection"},{"time":232000,"text":"to the cosmic event that we are part of,"},{"time":235000,"text":"and a story that is certainly ongoing."},{"time":237000,"text":"It's not something that has a good ending or a bad ending."},{"time":240000,"text":"It's actually a story in which our acts themselves"},{"time":243000,"text":"are pushing the story in a particular way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245000,"text":"So again I am a believer in the radical architecture."},{"time":248000,"text":"You know the Soviet architecture of that building"},{"time":250000,"text":"is the conservation."},{"time":252000,"text":"It's like the old Las Vegas used to be."},{"time":254000,"text":"It's about conserving emotions, conserving the traditions"},{"time":257000,"text":"that have obstructed the mind in moving forward"},{"time":259000,"text":"and of course what is radical is to confront them."},{"time":262000,"text":"And I think our architecture is a confrontation"},{"time":264000,"text":"with our own senses."},{"time":266000,"text":"Therefore I believe it should not be cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"There is a lot of appreciation for the kind of cool architecture."},{"time":272000,"text":"I've always been an opponent of it. I think emotion is needed."},{"time":275000,"text":"Life without emotion would really not be life."},{"time":278000,"text":"Even the mind is emotional."},{"time":280000,"text":"There is no reason which does not take a position"},{"time":282000,"text":"in the ethical sphere, in the philosophical mystery of what we are."},{"time":286000,"text":"So I think emotion is a dimension"},{"time":289000,"text":"that is important to introduce into city space, into city life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293000,"text":"And of course, we are all about the struggle of emotions."},{"time":296000,"text":"And I think that is what makes the world a wondrous place."},{"time":299000,"text":"And of course, the confrontation of the cool, the unemotional with emotion,"},{"time":303000,"text":"is a conversation that I think"},{"time":305000,"text":"cities themselves have fostered."},{"time":307000,"text":"I think that is the progress of cities."},{"time":309000,"text":"It's not only the forms of cities,"},{"time":311000,"text":"but the fact that they incarnate emotions,"},{"time":313000,"text":"not just of those who build them,"},{"time":315000,"text":"but of those who live there as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"Inexplicable versus understood. You know, too often we want to understand everything."},{"time":320000,"text":"But architecture is not the language of words."},{"time":323000,"text":"It's a language. But it is not a language that can be reduced"},{"time":327000,"text":"to a series of programmatic notes that we can verbally write."},{"time":330000,"text":"Too many buildings that you see outside that are so banal"},{"time":332000,"text":"tell you a story, but the story is very short,"},{"time":335000,"text":"which says, \"We have no story to tell you.\""},{"time":337000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"So the important thing actually,"},{"time":340000,"text":"is to introduce the actual architectural dimensions,"},{"time":343000,"text":"which might be totally inexplicable in words,"},{"time":346000,"text":"because they operate in proportions,"},{"time":349000,"text":"in materials, in light."},{"time":351000,"text":"They connect themselves into various sources,"},{"time":354000,"text":"into a kind of complex vector matrix"},{"time":356000,"text":"that isn't really frontal"},{"time":359000,"text":"but is really embedded in the lives,"},{"time":361000,"text":"and in the history of a city, and of a people."},{"time":364000,"text":"So again, the notion that a building should just be explicit"},{"time":367000,"text":"I think is a false notion,"},{"time":369000,"text":"which has reduced architecture into banality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371000,"text":"Hand versus the computer."},{"time":373000,"text":"Of course, what would we be without computers?"},{"time":375000,"text":"Our whole practice depends on computing."},{"time":377000,"text":"But the computer should not just be the glove of the hand;"},{"time":381000,"text":"the hand should really be the driver of the computing power."},{"time":385000,"text":"Because I believe that the hand"},{"time":387000,"text":"in all its primitive, in all its physiological obscurity,"},{"time":392000,"text":"has a source, though the source is unknown,"},{"time":395000,"text":"though we don't have to be mystical about it."},{"time":397000,"text":"We realize that the hand has been given us"},{"time":400000,"text":"by forces that are beyond our own autonomy."},{"time":403000,"text":"And I think when I draw drawings"},{"time":406000,"text":"which may imitate the computer, but are not computer drawings --"},{"time":409000,"text":"drawings that can come from sources"},{"time":411000,"text":"that are completely not known, not normal, not seen,"},{"time":415000,"text":"yet the hand -- and that's what I really, to all of you who are working --"},{"time":419000,"text":"how can we make the computer respond to our hand"},{"time":423000,"text":"rather than the hand responding to the computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"I think that's part of what the complexity of architecture is."},{"time":430000,"text":"Because certainly we have gotten used to the propaganda"},{"time":434000,"text":"that the simple is the good. But I don't believe it."},{"time":436000,"text":"Listening to all of you, the complexity of thought,"},{"time":439000,"text":"the complexity of layers of meaning is overwhelming."},{"time":442000,"text":"And I think we shouldn't shy away in architecture,"},{"time":445000,"text":"You know, brain surgery, atomic theory,"},{"time":448000,"text":"genetics, economics"},{"time":451000,"text":"are complex complex fields."},{"time":453000,"text":"There is no reason that architecture should shy away"},{"time":455000,"text":"and present this illusory world of the simple."},{"time":458000,"text":"It is complex. Space is complex."},{"time":460000,"text":"Space is something that folds out of itself into completely new worlds."},{"time":464000,"text":"And as wondrous as it is,"},{"time":466000,"text":"it cannot be reduced to a kind of simplification"},{"time":469000,"text":"that we have often come to be admired."},{"time":471000,"text":"And yet, our lives are complex."},{"time":473000,"text":"Our emotions are complex."},{"time":475000,"text":"Our intellectual desires are complex."},{"time":477000,"text":"So I do believe that architecture as I see it"},{"time":480000,"text":"needs to mirror that complexity in every single space that we have,"},{"time":484000,"text":"in every intimacy that we possess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"Of course that means that architecture is political."},{"time":489000,"text":"The political is not an enemy of architecture."},{"time":491000,"text":"The politeama is the city. It's all of us together."},{"time":494000,"text":"And I've always believed that the act of architecture,"},{"time":496000,"text":"even a private house, when somebody else will see it, is a political act,"},{"time":500000,"text":"because it will be visible to others."},{"time":502000,"text":"And we live in a world which is connecting us more and more."},{"time":504000,"text":"So again, the evasion of that sphere,"},{"time":508000,"text":"which has been so endemic to that sort of pure architecture,"},{"time":511000,"text":"the autonomous architecture that is just an abstract object"},{"time":513000,"text":"has never appealed to me."},{"time":515000,"text":"And I do believe that this interaction"},{"time":518000,"text":"with the history, with history that is often very difficult,"},{"time":522000,"text":"to grapple with it, to create"},{"time":524000,"text":"a position that is beyond our normal expectations and to create a critique."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"Because architecture is also the asking of questions."},{"time":532000,"text":"It's not only the giving of answers."},{"time":534000,"text":"It's also, just like life, the asking of questions."},{"time":537000,"text":"Therefore it is important that it be real."},{"time":539000,"text":"You know we can simulate almost anything."},{"time":541000,"text":"But the one thing that can be ever simulated"},{"time":543000,"text":"is the human heart, the human soul."},{"time":546000,"text":"And architecture is so closely intertwined with it"},{"time":548000,"text":"because we are born somewhere and we die somewhere."},{"time":551000,"text":"So the reality of architecture is visceral. It's not intellectual."},{"time":555000,"text":"It's not something that comes to us from books and theories."},{"time":558000,"text":"It's the real that we touch -- the door, the window,"},{"time":562000,"text":"the threshold, the bed --"},{"time":564000,"text":"such prosaic objects. And yet,"},{"time":566000,"text":"I try, in every building, to take that virtual world,"},{"time":568000,"text":"which is so enigmatic and so rich,"},{"time":571000,"text":"and create something in the real world."},{"time":573000,"text":"Create a space for an office,"},{"time":575000,"text":"a space of sustainability"},{"time":577000,"text":"that really works between that virtuality"},{"time":580000,"text":"and yet can be realized as something real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"Unexpected versus habitual."},{"time":584000,"text":"What is a habit? It's just a shackle for ourselves."},{"time":587000,"text":"It's a self-induced poison."},{"time":589000,"text":"So the unexpected is always unexpected."},{"time":591000,"text":"You know, it's true, the cathedrals, as unexpected,"},{"time":594000,"text":"will always be unexpected."},{"time":596000,"text":"You know Frank Gehry's buildings, they will continue to be unexpected in the future."},{"time":599000,"text":"So not the habitual architecture that instills in us"},{"time":602000,"text":"the false sort of stability,"},{"time":604000,"text":"but an architecture that is full of tension,"},{"time":607000,"text":"an architecture that goes beyond itself"},{"time":610000,"text":"to reach a human soul and a human heart,"},{"time":612000,"text":"and that breaks out of the shackles of habits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615000,"text":"And of course habits are enforced by architecture."},{"time":618000,"text":"When we see the same kind of architecture"},{"time":620000,"text":"we become immured in that world of those angles,"},{"time":623000,"text":"of those lights, of those materials."},{"time":625000,"text":"We think the world really looks like our buildings."},{"time":628000,"text":"And yet our buildings are pretty much limited by the techniques and wonders"},{"time":632000,"text":"that have been part of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"So again, the unexpected which is also the raw."},{"time":637000,"text":"And I often think of the raw and the refined."},{"time":639000,"text":"What is raw? The raw, I would say"},{"time":641000,"text":"is the naked experience, untouched by luxury,"},{"time":644000,"text":"untouched by expensive materials,"},{"time":646000,"text":"untouched by the kind of refinement"},{"time":648000,"text":"that we associate with high culture."},{"time":651000,"text":"So the rawness, I think, in space,"},{"time":654000,"text":"the fact that sustainability can actually, in the future"},{"time":657000,"text":"translate into a raw space,"},{"time":659000,"text":"a space that isn't decorated,"},{"time":661000,"text":"a space that is not mannered in any source,"},{"time":664000,"text":"but a space that might be cool in terms of its temperature,"},{"time":668000,"text":"might be refractive to our desires."},{"time":671000,"text":"A space that doesn't always follow us"},{"time":674000,"text":"like a dog that has been trained to follow us,"},{"time":677000,"text":"but moves ahead into directions of demonstrating"},{"time":680000,"text":"other possibilities, other experiences,"},{"time":682000,"text":"that have never been part of the vocabulary of architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"And of course that juxtaposition is of great interest to me"},{"time":690000,"text":"because it creates a kind of a spark of new energy."},{"time":694000,"text":"And so I do like something which is pointed, not blunt,"},{"time":697000,"text":"something which is focused on reality,"},{"time":700000,"text":"something that has the power, through its leverage,"},{"time":703000,"text":"to transform even a very small space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"So architecture maybe is not so big, like science,"},{"time":708000,"text":"but through its focal point"},{"time":711000,"text":"it can leverage in an Archimedian way"},{"time":713000,"text":"what we think the world is really about."},{"time":715000,"text":"And often it takes just a building"},{"time":717000,"text":"to change our experience of what could be done, what has been done,"},{"time":721000,"text":"how the world has remained both in between stability and instability."},{"time":726000,"text":"And of course buildings have their shapes."},{"time":729000,"text":"Those shapes are difficult to change."},{"time":731000,"text":"And yet, I do believe that in every social space,"},{"time":733000,"text":"in every public space,"},{"time":735000,"text":"there is a desire to communicate more"},{"time":737000,"text":"than just that blunt thought, that blunt technique,"},{"time":741000,"text":"but something that pinpoints, and can point in various directions"},{"time":745000,"text":"forward, backward, sideways and around."},{"time":748000,"text":"So that is indeed what is memory."},{"time":751000,"text":"So I believe that my main interest is to memory."},{"time":755000,"text":"Without memory we would be amnesiacs."},{"time":757000,"text":"We would not know which way we were going,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and why we are going where we're going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761000,"text":"So I've been never interested in the forgettable reuse,"},{"time":766000,"text":"rehashing of the same things over and over again,"},{"time":769000,"text":"which, of course, get accolades of critics."},{"time":771000,"text":"Critics like the performance to be repeated again and again the same way."},{"time":775000,"text":"But I rather play something"},{"time":777000,"text":"completely unheard of,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and even with flaws,"},{"time":781000,"text":"than repeat the same thing over and over which has been hollowed"},{"time":783000,"text":"by its meaninglessness."},{"time":785000,"text":"So again, memory is the city, memory is the world."},{"time":788000,"text":"Without the memory there would be no story to tell."},{"time":790000,"text":"There would be nowhere to turn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"The memorable, I think, is really our world, what we think the world is."},{"time":796000,"text":"And it's not only our memory,"},{"time":798000,"text":"but those who remember us,"},{"time":801000,"text":"which means that architecture is not mute."},{"time":803000,"text":"It's an art of communication."},{"time":805000,"text":"It tells a story. The story can reach into obscure desires."},{"time":809000,"text":"It can reach into sources that are not explicitly available."},{"time":812000,"text":"It can reach into millennia"},{"time":815000,"text":"that have been buried,"},{"time":817000,"text":"and return them in a just and unexpected equity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821000,"text":"So again, I think the notion that"},{"time":823000,"text":"the best architecture is silent has never appealed to me."},{"time":827000,"text":"Silence maybe is good for a cemetery but not for a city."},{"time":830000,"text":"Cities should be full of vibrations, full of sound, full of music."},{"time":833000,"text":"And that indeed is the architectural mission"},{"time":835000,"text":"that I believe is important,"},{"time":837000,"text":"is to create spaces that are vibrant,"},{"time":839000,"text":"that are pluralistic,"},{"time":841000,"text":"that can transform the most prosaic activities,"},{"time":844000,"text":"and raise them to a completely different expectation."},{"time":846000,"text":"Create a shopping center, a swimming place"},{"time":848000,"text":"that is more like a museum than like entertainment."},{"time":851000,"text":"And these are our dreams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"And of course risk. I think architecture should be risky."},{"time":857000,"text":"You know it costs a lot of money and so on, but yes,"},{"time":859000,"text":"it should not play it safe."},{"time":861000,"text":"It should not play it safe, because if it plays it safe"},{"time":864000,"text":"it's not moving us in a direction that we want to be."},{"time":868000,"text":"And I think, of course,"},{"time":870000,"text":"risk is what underlies the world."},{"time":872000,"text":"World without risk would not be worth living."},{"time":875000,"text":"So yes, I do believe that the risk we take in every building."},{"time":879000,"text":"Risks to create spaces that have never been cantilevered to that extent."},{"time":883000,"text":"Risks of spaces that have never been"},{"time":885000,"text":"so dizzying,"},{"time":888000,"text":"as they should be, for a pioneering city."},{"time":891000,"text":"Risks that really move architecture"},{"time":894000,"text":"even with all its flaws, into a space which is much better"},{"time":897000,"text":"that the ever again repeated"},{"time":899000,"text":"hollowness of a ready-made thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"And of course that is finally what I believe architecture to be."},{"time":905000,"text":"It's about space. It's not about fashion."},{"time":907000,"text":"It's not about decoration."},{"time":909000,"text":"It's about creating with minimal means"},{"time":911000,"text":"something which can not be repeated,"},{"time":914000,"text":"cannot be simulated in any other sphere."},{"time":916000,"text":"And there of course is the space that we need to breathe,"},{"time":920000,"text":"is the space we need to dream."},{"time":922000,"text":"These are the spaces that are"},{"time":924000,"text":"not just luxurious spaces for some of us,"},{"time":927000,"text":"but are important for everybody in this world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"So again, it's not about the changing fashions, changing theories."},{"time":933000,"text":"It's about carving out a space for trees."},{"time":936000,"text":"It's carving out a space where nature can enter"},{"time":938000,"text":"the domestic world of a city."},{"time":940000,"text":"A space where something which has never seen a light of day"},{"time":944000,"text":"can enter into the inner workings of a density."},{"time":948000,"text":"And I think that is really the nature of architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"Now I am a believer in democracy."},{"time":954000,"text":"I don't like beautiful buildings"},{"time":956000,"text":"built for totalitarian regimes."},{"time":958000,"text":"Where people cannot speak, cannot vote, cannot do anything."},{"time":960000,"text":"We too often admire those buildings. We think they are beautiful."},{"time":963000,"text":"And yet when I think of the poverty of society"},{"time":965000,"text":"which doesn't give freedom to its people,"},{"time":967000,"text":"I don't admire those buildings."},{"time":969000,"text":"So democracy, as difficult as it is, I believe in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971000,"text":"And of course, at Ground Zero what else?"},{"time":974000,"text":"It's such a complex project."},{"time":976000,"text":"It's emotional. There is so many interests."},{"time":978000,"text":"It's political. There is so many parties to this project."},{"time":982000,"text":"There is so many interests. There's money. There's political power."},{"time":984000,"text":"There are emotions of the victims."},{"time":986000,"text":"And yet, in all its messiness, in all its difficulties,"},{"time":990000,"text":"I would not have liked somebody to say,"},{"time":992000,"text":"\"This is the tabula rasa, mister architect -- do whatever you want.\""},{"time":995000,"text":"I think nothing good will come out of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997000,"text":"I think architecture is about consensus."},{"time":999000,"text":"And it is about the dirty word \"compromise.\" Compromise is not bad."},{"time":1003000,"text":"Compromise, if it's artistic,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"if it is able to cope with its strategies --"},{"time":1008000,"text":"and there is my first sketch and the last rendering --"},{"time":1010000,"text":"it's not that far away."},{"time":1012000,"text":"And yet, compromise, consensus,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"that is what I believe in."},{"time":1016000,"text":"And Ground Zero, despite all its difficulties, it's moving forward."},{"time":1019000,"text":"It's difficult. 2011, 2013. Freedom Tower, the memorial."},{"time":1024000,"text":"And that is where I end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026000,"text":"I was inspired when I came here as an immigrant"},{"time":1028000,"text":"on a ship like millions of others,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"looking at America from that point of view."},{"time":1033000,"text":"This is America. This is liberty."},{"time":1035000,"text":"This is what we dream about. Its individuality,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"demonstrated in the skyline. It's resilience."},{"time":1040000,"text":"And finally, it's the freedom that America represents,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"not just to me, as an immigrant, but to everyone in the world. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051000,"text":"Chris Anderson: I've got a question."},{"time":1053000,"text":"So have you come to peace"},{"time":1055000,"text":"with the process that happened at Ground Zero"},{"time":1058000,"text":"and the loss of the original, incredible design that you came up with?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1061000,"text":"Daniel Libeskind: Look. We have to cure ourselves"},{"time":1065000,"text":"of the notion that we are authoritarian,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"that we can determine everything that happens."},{"time":1069000,"text":"We have to rely on others, and shape the process in the best way possible."},{"time":1073000,"text":"I came from the Bronx. I was taught not to be a loser,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"not to be somebody who just gives up in a fight."},{"time":1078000,"text":"You have to fight for what you believe. You don't always win"},{"time":1080000,"text":"everything you want to win. But you can steer the process."},{"time":1083000,"text":"And I believe that what will be built at Ground Zero"},{"time":1086000,"text":"will be meaningful, will be inspiring,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"will tell other generations of the sacrifices,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"of the meaning of this event."},{"time":1093000,"text":"Not just for New York, but for the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1095000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you so much, Daniel Libeskind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1097000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}